verbose_text: During 1 January-30 April 2020, the NOAA NCEP / NCAR reanalysis for evaluating the atmospheric capability to disperse air pollutants provided satellite vertical airflows Omega surface charts at 850 mb (~ 1.5 km above sea level) and 950 mb (~ 0.762 km above sea level), which recorded downwards airflows described by positive omega values.
